transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thank you for calling Viagra. How can I help you today?

Speaker 2: Yeah, how you doing?

Speaker 1: I'm doing well, sir. How can I help you?

Speaker 2: Good, good. Um, yeah, I just got in and I received my prescription.

Speaker 1: The thing is, though, is it's short by about ten.

Speaker 2: I could take a look to see what's going on. What's your last name and a zip code?

Speaker 1: Last name is Martinez, M-A-R-T-I-N-E-Z. Zip code is 9-2-5-0-5.

Speaker 2: All right, give me a moment here.

Speaker 1: Take your time.

Speaker 2: And how many pills did you receive?

Speaker 1: I only got 30 in the container. I was supposed to get 40.

Speaker 2: All right, give me a moment here to see what's going on.

Speaker 1: Okay. Um, I see here there wasn't really too many notes left on here,

Speaker 2: but I do see they had sent you a new order out.

Speaker 1: I can't really validate anything on my side,

Speaker 2: so at this point we're just going to kind of go with in good faith that you're saying you got 30.

Speaker 1: So I'm just going to notify the pharmacy to ship out an additional ten.

Speaker 2: Okay. Now, I got another question for you.

Speaker 1: This was only a one-time purchase, correct?

Speaker 2: This is an order you placed that has to come with a set date to remain active.

Speaker 1: Without that, you wouldn't be able to order in the future,

Speaker 2: or this order wouldn't be able to ship out.

Speaker 1: It needs to have the prescriptions because they're through Pfizer.

Speaker 2: They need to have a refill date to stay active.

Speaker 1: Without the refill dates, the pharmacy can't ship anything out.

Speaker 2: I see that you spoke to someone on the 12th of January,

Speaker 1: and you had agreed upon setting it for five months out from now to freeze it out.

Speaker 2: Wait a minute. I agreed to what now?

Speaker 1: To just freeze out any future orders for five months.

Speaker 2: That way you could try these out and see if you're a fan,

Speaker 1: and then call us back to finalize any choice.

Speaker 2: Ah, okay. So my date is when did I have to call you? By what?

Speaker 1: Call us before July, basically.

Speaker 2: Okay, okay. And that way it won't be what I'm looking for.

Speaker 1: Yeah, no, no worries.

Speaker 2: Yeah, that way you don't have to be waiting for the packages to show up.

Speaker 1: Just call us once you try them out, if you're a fan of them.

Speaker 2: Great. We'll change your frequency to match your preference.

Speaker 1: Okay.

Speaker 2: All right.

Speaker 1: All right. You try to do the same.

Speaker 2: And you said you're going to have them send them out?

Speaker 1: Yeah, they'll send them out. You'll get a package with 10 in there.

Speaker 2: Okay, perfect.

Speaker 1: All right. Thank you, sir. You have a good day now.

Speaker 2: You too. Have a good day.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Bye-bye.
